@NODE ChkWin "ChkWin V1.00 by Codex Design Software"

                                  @{b}@{u}CHKWIN@{ub}@{uu}

 @{b}Task:@{ub}

ChkWin  is  a  little  commodity that allows you to determine which process
controls a window by pressing a user-definable hotkey.  It might be used to
define @{"user-settings" LINK Settings} for some windows...;)

 @{b}Start:@{ub}

Double-click or enter name in CLI.

 @{b}Tooltypes/CLI options:@{ub}

CX_POPUP: Immediately pop up information requester when starting.
CX_HOTKEY: Keystroke to invoke chkwin for active window.
CX_PRI: Priority of commodity.

 @{b}Bugs:@{ub}

None known.

 @{b}Notes:@{ub}

reqtools.library © Nico François will be used if available.
@ENDNODE

